<Content_wSideColumn ID="x53509" Name="Advising" Layout="byuidefault.xsl"><Title type="string" label="Title" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="true">Advising</Title><Abstract type="string" label="Abstract" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="true">Advising</Abstract><xPower Type="GroupStart" GroupStart="" Name="SideColumn" label="L/R Column" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false" Expanded="false"><MoveLeft type="boolean" hidden="true" label="Toggle column right or left (right is default)" readonly="false" required="false">false</MoveLeft><xPower Type="Component" Component="" Name="ImageComponent" label="Image Component" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false" CompTypes="LeftColumnImageComponent"/><xPower Type="Component" Component="" Name="TextComponent" label="Text Component" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false" CompTypes="ColumnTextComponent"/></xPower><BodyCopy type="dhtml" label="Body Copy" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false"><![CDATA[<p>Information regarding course planning for <a href="http://www.byui.edu/academic-discovery-center/students/academic-advising-and-class-planning/class-planning/recommended-course-sequences/business-and-communication#2">Business Management majors</a> is available online.  You may also visit with our advising staff in SMI 227 or send them an email at <a href="mailto:businessadv@byui.edu"><span style="color: #3300ff;">businessadv@byui.edu</span></a>. You may also contact them by phone at 208-496-9840.</p>
<p>A Grad Planning Lab is also available Fridays from 9-4 in SMI 223.  If you would like, you may <a href="http://www.byui.edu/academic-discovery-center/students/academic-advising-and-class-planning/class-planning/the-graduation-planner">work on your own grad plan</a> ahead of time and then have the advisors review it with you.</p>
<p>Catalog year 2012 - our <a href="Documents/business-communication/New Degree Brochure(0).pdf">new standard degree program</a> map and <a href="Documents/business-communication/Brochure Business Management Concentration.pdf">concentration degree</a> map can be found here.  This program is for incoming freshman Fall 2012 and all those who change their graduation catalog to 2012.</p>
<p>Catalog years 2009-2011 map of the Business Management program can also be found <span style="color: #3300cc;"><a href="Documents/Colleges_and_Departments/Business_and_Communication/Business_Management/Business%20Map.pdf">here</a></span></p>
